                  but helped by an angel he escapes the punishment.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusFrom/><betmas:locusTo/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient718/msitem/ms_i1.7.20"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Lālibalā runs away to the desert with Masqal Kǝbrā.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusFrom/><betmas:locusTo/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient718/msitem/ms_i1.7.21"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>After their prayers for food, Lālibalā and Masqal Kǝbrā find partridges which
